text: San Naing (born March 5, 1991) is a Burmese long-distance runner. He competed at the 2016 Summer Olympics in the men's 5000 metres race; his time of 15:51.05 in the heats did not qualify him for the final. ==References== Category:1991 births Category:Living people Category:Burmese male long- distance runners Category:Olympic athletes of Myanmar Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 2016 Summer Olympics Category:Southeast Asian Games medalists in athletics Category:Southeast Asian Games bronze medalists for Myanmar Category:Competitors at the 2015 Southeast Asian Games
